com.solacesystems.solclientj.core.event

Interface FlowEventCallback


  • public interface FlowEventCallback
    The callback interface for Flow events. The callback with this interface is registered for a Flow when the flow is created SessionHandle.createFlowForHandle() It is called for each Flow event that occurs.

    When a Flow event is received that indicates an error condition (such as a bind failure), additional error information is recorded and can be retrieved through SolClient.getLastErrorInfo() :

    • COMMUNICATION_ERROR - The underlying connection failed
    • PROTOCOL_ERROR - A protocol error occurred between the API and the Appliance.
    • KEEP_ALIVE_FAILURE - The Session went down due to a Keep-Alive failure.
    • TIMEOUT - A timeout occurred on an operation such as binding to a Flow.
    See Also:
